snippet: While tensions and violence appear to be rising, most commentators say the conditions are different from those of the previous Palestinian uprisings.
abstract: News analysis; tensions between Palestinians and Jews are intensifying discussion of whether violence that has gripped East Jerusalem, fueled by struggle over site in the Old City sacred to both Jews and Muslims, amounts to third intifada, or uprising, by Palestinians against Israeli occupation; most commentators hold that current unrest lacks the coordinated leadership, momentum and mass participation of an intifada.

byline.contributor: Majd Al Waheidi contributed reporting from Gaza.

lead_paragraph: While tensions and violence appear to be rising, most commentators say the conditions are different from those of the previous Palestinian uprisings.

headline.main: In Jerusalem Unrest, Signs of a ‘Run-Over Intifada’ for the 21st Century
headline.print_headline: In Jerusalem Unrest, Signs of a ‘Run-Over Intifada’ for the 21st Century
